model

Class HeadmasterCustomer

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.User
      • model.HeadmasterCustomer

  • public class HeadmasterCustomer
extends User
    HeadmasterCustomer class represent an user who is the holder of a musical school; it extends User class and automatically set the type as TITOLARE.
    Version:
    1.4
    Author:
    Paolo D'Arienzo

                   throws java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException
        Constructor of HeadmasterCustomer; ignores the param TipoCliente passed because it's always TITOLARE.
        Parameters:
        mail - is the e-mail of the user
        nomeUtente - is the nickname of the user
        password - stores the encrypted password of the user
        nome - is the name of the user
        cognome - is the surname of the user
        numeroTelefono - is the telephone number of the user
        cittaDiResidenza - is the city in which resides the user
        CF - is the fiscal code of the user
        tipoCliente - indicates the type of user; it's always TITOLARE
        numeroCellulare - is the private telephone number of the user
        Throws:
        java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException - if an error occurs with the encryption of the password, i.e. the algorithm used for the encryption can't be found
